Babu Frik Help Menu
Syntax: ~kick <member> [reason]
Kick a user.
Examples:
  • ~kick 428675506947227648 wanted to be kicked. This will kick the user with ID 428675506947227648 from the server.
  • ~kick @Twentysix wanted to be kicked. This will kick Twentysix from the server.
If a reason is specified, it will be the reason that shows up in the audit log.
Type ~help <command> for more info on a command. You can also type ~help <category> for more info on a category.
